{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772048173,"nonce":"3SudW9DMneVGOFVexv9mZEFQrzE=","title":"NN internal uniformity \u0026 interpretability (single state vs Penzai core)","message":"[Imported from GitHub #41] (created 2026-01-26T17:44:07Z)\n\n## Summary\nDefine a **uniform, interpretable internal representation for neural networks** inside Feedbax, while preserving the graph-based outer model (cycles/feedback). The goal is to make NN internals inspectable and editable without adopting a second state system (e.g., Penzai core), unless the benefits outweigh the complexity.\n\n## Context / Motivation\n- The outer architecture must remain a **graph** (cycles/feedback). Trees are insufficient at that level.\n- NN internals are naturally **hierarchical** and can be represented as a tree for inspection/surgery.\n- We want **interpretability tooling** (selectors, visualization) for NN internals without splitting state paradigms.\n\n## Proposed Direction (Single State System)\n- Keep Equinox + `StateIndex` as the **single state system** across the codebase.\n- Add a **canonical NN internal tree** (e.g., `nn_tree()` + metadata: tags/roles), used for selectors + visualization.\n- Treat the NN tree as **source-of-truth** for interpretability and surgery, not just a debug artifact.\n\n## Why not Penzai core (for now)\n- Penzai introduces **variable objects** and a second state system. Even if functionalized, it’s a conceptual boundary.\n- Using Penzai only for NNs creates mixed paradigms and potentially a “black-box boundary” at the NN component.\n- Most benefits (hierarchical uniformity, selectors, inspection) can be achieved with a canonical NN tree + selectors/Treescope.\n\n## When switching to Penzai core *might* make sense\n- We need **Penzai’s variable objects** (parameter/state nodes, parameter tying) as first-class tools.\n- We want **Penzai’s uniform layer interface** enforced across all NN internals and are willing to adopt its style.\n- We find the internal NN tree/metadata approach is too fragile or expensive to maintain.\n- We want direct compatibility with Penzai interpretability workflows beyond selectors/Treescope.\n\n## Acceptance / Next Steps\n- [ ] Prototype one NN module with a canonical `nn_tree()` representation.\n- [ ] Validate selectors + Treescope on that tree (simple edit + visualization).\n- [ ] Evaluate whether “single-state + tree metadata” gives enough interpretability.\n- [ ] Revisit Penzai core only if the prototype is not compelling.\n\n## Notes\n- Outer system remains a **graph**; NN tree is an internal representation only.\n- This issue is about **uniformity + interpretability for NN internals**, not global architecture.\n\n---\nCo-Authored-By: GPT-5 \u003cnoreply@openai.com\u003e","files":null}]}